text: John Reynolds was an English Anglican priest in the 17th century."Catalogue of the Lansdowne Manuscripts in the British Museum" p248: London; British Museum ; 1819 Reynolds was born in Southampton and educated at Merton College, Oxford.Alumni Oxonienses 1500-1714, Rabbetts-Rhodes He was incorporated at Cambridge in 1633.Alumni Cantabrigienses He was Archdeacon of Norwich from 1668 until 1676. ==Notes== Category:People from Southampton}} Category:17th- century English Anglican priests Category:Archdeacons of Norfolk Category:Alumni of Merton College, Oxford
title: John Reynolds (priest)
